<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900717-0108</DOCNO><DOCID>900717-0108.</DOCID><HL>   Canadian Government Bond Sale</HL><DATE>07/17/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C21</SO><CO>   CANDA</CO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</IN><LP>   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.6billion Canadian dollars (US$1.38 billion) of bonds in fourissues this week.   Its sale will involve 11.75% bonds due Oct. 15, 1993;10.75% bonds due Dec. 15, 1995; 10.50% bonds due July 1,2000; and 10.25% bonds due March 15, 2014. Offering terms areto be announced today.</LP><TEXT>   The Bank of Canada has agreed to purchase at least C$100million of the new bonds. The remainder will be available topublic investors.   Proceeds will be used to redeem C$1.53 billion of bondsmaturing Aug. 1 and for general government purposes.</TEXT></DOC>